        "I was fiddling around with a cluster of 3 RethinkDB instances running locally. Populating data into this cluster from the Twitter Streaming API. I see a write rate of around 80 writes/sec. Now when fiddling in the Rethink Admin Console, and changing the 'Sharding Settings', I immediately see a write failure on my streaming app.\n\n```\nRqlRuntimeError: Cannot perform write: lost contact with master in:\nr.db(\"twitter\").table(\"samples\").insert({delete: {status: {id: 154386386936537100, id_str: \"154386386936537088\", user_id: 382981485, user_id_str: \"382981485\"}, timestamp_ms: \"1415010297245\"}})\n```\n\nThe little app I'm using looks like this:\n\n``` js\nvar util = require('util'),\n    twitter = require('twitter'),\n    r = require('rethinkdb');\nvar twit = new twitter({\n    consumer_key: '123',\n    consumer_secret: '123',\n    access_token_key: '123',\n    access_token_secret: '123'\n});\n\nvar connection = null;\nr.connect( {host: \"localhost\", port: 28015}, function(err, conn) {\n    if (err) throw err;\n    connection = conn;\n\n    // r.db('twitter').tableCreate('samples').run(connection, function(err, result) {\n    //     if (err) throw err;\n    //     console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n\n        twit.stream('statuses/sample', function(stream) {\n            stream.on('data', function(data) {\n                // console.log(util.inspect(data));\n\n                r.db('twitter').table('samples').insert(data).run(connection, function(err, result) {\n                    if (err) throw err;\n                    console.log(JSON.stringify(result, null, 2));\n                });\n\n            });\n\n            stream.on('error', function(error) {\n                throw error;\n            });\n        });\n\n    // });\n});\n\n```\n\nI tried both increasing sharding value from say 1 to 3, or back to 1 from 3. And in both cases I noticed this write failure. Not aware of the internals, but thought it would be good to share this with the team.\n"
